As an introverted, privacy-conscious creative entrepreneur running my own business, it shouldn't feel so awkward, but sometimes it does. Most online resources and mentors tell you to interact with big (evil) tech companies in an extroverted way. Advertise here, follow algorithms, share your personality charm. Get verified on that service, stay online all day, answer questions with your own videos, and respond immediately. Videos, videos, and more videos.
1/3
This year is a transformation year for me.
I don't want to continue dedicating my money, data, and energy to big tech companies, nor do I want to listen to mentors who only apply a single extroverted solution to everyone. I am exploring new business models while also working to overcome my long-held belief that success can only be achieved by doing things in a specific way.
Good luck to me!
The first step has been taken.
I left FB, removed all Meta and Pinterest trackers from my website, and canceled my personal WhatsApp account.
Yesterday, I also removed the last external tracker from my website - Google Analytics, and felt great.
To better support GDPR, I recently subscribed to a European CRM service and will migrate my business there over the next few weeks.
I transferred my MX records to Proton, and now have complete SPF, DKIM, and DMARC, without having to pay Google for basic email verification anymore.
3/3
